name: Atum
title: Atum - The Self-Created God | Egyptian Mythology
subtitle:
The Complete One
     
     , First God, Setting Sun
shortDescription: Atum is the self-created primordial deity who emerged from the waters of Nun at creation. He represents completion and the setting sun. Often merged with Ra as Atum - Ra , he masturbated or spat to create Shu (air) and Tefnut (moisture), beginning the Ennead . He is both the first and last god, present at creation and at the end of time.
